28-29 March - Lasagna with Salsa Besciamella

Salsa Besciamella
- 8     tablespoon butter
- 3/4   cup flour
- 1/2   teaspoon salt
- 3 1/2 cup scalded milk
-       white pepper
-       fresh nutmeg

Melt butter over medium heat. Blend in flour and salt and stir with whisk until mixture foams (about 4 minutes). Add the milk stirring rapidly with whisk. COok over low flame for 5-10 minutes until mixture has consistency of thin pudding. Add nutmeg, salt and pepper. Let it cool about 10 minutes before using. It becomes firmer as it cools.

Lasagna

- 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese
- 3/4 cup grated mozzarella
-     lasagna pasta
-     meat sauce
-     salsa besciamella

Toss cheeses together with fork to mix completely. Generously butter bottom and sides of a 9x13" pan and place lasagna strips in bottom so that they hang 3" over the edge of the pan on all four sides. Spread pasta with meat sauce, sprinkle with grated cheese and pour a thin coating of besciamella on meat sauce and cheese. With pasta strips cover and repeat twice more. Fold strips over, top with besciamella, bake at 450F. 